>NAME

setgid - set group IDs

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <sys/types.h>
	#include <unistd.h>
	
	int setgid(gid_t 'gid');

>DESCRIPTION

This function changes group IDs. If the current effective group ID is 0 ('root'), then 'gid' can have any value, and the effective, saved, and real group IDs are all set to 'gid'. Otherwise, 'gid' must be the current effective or real group ID, and the effective group ID is changed to 'gid'.

>RETURN VALUE

This function returns '0' on success, or '-1' on error and sets [errno.6] appropriately.

>ERRORS

On error, this function returns '-1' and sets [errno.6] to one of the following values:

\* *EPERM* - the current effective group ID is nonzero and 'gid' does not match the current effective or real group ID.

